The survivors' committee forms in a schoolyard with your people holding the clipboards, and refuses the quick signatures en bloc. The indemnities triple; the count climbs toward honesty; and in the colonias of the north rim, the lesson files itself next to all the others: the state counts its own disasters the way it counts votes.

@denuncia_sj
go-to: post_event
on-arrival: sup_middle += 2; political_capital += 2; expediente += 2

The dossier — siting maps, the 1979 inspection nobody acted on, the hydrant lines that carried no water — runs in the weekly and is read into the tribune. Nothing is prosecuted; everything is remembered. Ten months later, when the earth itself takes up the argument, the Republic will already have the vocabulary.
